    "en": {
      "title": "Indian fuel for Sri Lankan aircraft",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Following the fuel shortage in Sri Lanka, the Indian state-owned Bharat Petroleum Corporation (BPC) has informed SriLankan Airlines for refuelling.",
        "About 100 Sri Lankan planes have been refueled at Thiruvananthapuram, Chennai and Kochi airports so far.",
        "Bharat Petroleum stated that this refueling has been done at very short notice for more than a fortnight. It is noteworthy that SriLankan Airlines has also expressed its gratitude for this service of India."
      ],
